    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-04T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/7760: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-04T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 4, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>433. The Department concurs in the opinion expressed in your 531, March 26, 9
                    a.m. At a conference of representatives of State and Treasury Departments with
                    officers of War Department proposed new approach was discussed and approved.</p>
                <p>Department continues to have in mind effect on Chinese economy of expenditures
                    and hopes that you will be able to keep before our Army officers importance of
                    having Chinese Government assume as much responsibility for execution of program
                    as feasible in order that expenditures may be kept to a minimum consistent with
                    strategical considerations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
